history.text: Hi there!
Hi
So we'll be talking about Zootopia, right?
Yes.
I remember seeing this movie and it being pretty good
Me too
It's surprising that it has a 98% on Rotten Tomatoes
I liked it. I would have given it that rating. I agree with the reviews that it was funny, smart, and thought provoking
I agree with those reviews too, all of the actors and actresses did a great job
What did you think of the town names? I think they are clever. How about you?
I think so too! Definitely fits the characters and gives a good sense of the world
Yeah. What did you think of the scene where we find out that Nick was bullied as a kid?
I thought it was really touching and sad, I connected with that scene
It had a lot to say about how we treat others
Me too. It makes you understand his character more. It's good back story.
Definitely, it helps you to sympathize with his character
Totally. And it helps you understand, too, why he stands up for Judy and tells Bogo to let her finish solving the case.
A really cool character
The scene with the wolves was really suspensful
It was. It made sense that they would be the "night howlers." And it was a nice scary addition to the story.
Yeah, it added a good amount of tension in the story. It felt all the more exciting when Judy ends up solving the case.
Yeah. I felt bad for her, though, in the scene where she has to quit her job.
Yeah, that was really sad
I think the worst part was that she upset Nick who was becoming her friend, and she could see that her words were hurtful.
It was definitely a very valuable lesson in being mindful of what you say and how complicated relationships can be
Yeah. It worked out in the end though. Were you surprised when Bellweather turned out to be the mastermind of the predators going "savage?"
Absolutely, it was a pretty big shock. He really turned out to be seriously evil.
Yeah. I didn't see that coming. The character really is played as mild-mannered and sweet.
Just goes to show that it's always the quiet ones haha
Yeah! It was cool how it came full circle, too, with Judy recording the confession at the end
It was a thrilling end and definitely pulled everything together nicely
Definitely. It was a pretty enjoyable movie all around.
I agree! Well, thanks for chatting!
You too.
Take care! :)
